<h3 id="pixhell">Pixhell</h3>

<p><q>In a far away place exists a pocket of a world where tiny creatures draw out their inexplicably troubled lives. These are their stories.</q></p>
<p>I built these tiny animations using a hacked <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resource_fork#Major_resource_types" "The Wikipedia entry for resource forks.">CICN</a> editor in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ResEdit" title="The Wikipedia entry for ResEdit.">ResEdit</a> (oh, I know). I'd draw each frame pixel by pixel, carefully take a screenshot and paste it into an animated GIF editor.</p>
<p>When all the frames were done - and an episode could take up to <em>sixty hours</em> - I'd convert the GIF into a movie and send it over to my pal Kurt, who would create sound effects to match. Once I had his audio track I'd glue the two together and foist the episode onto the Interwebs.</p>
<p>I've kept the original, painful descriptions.</p>

